Added: There is now an additional overload of
Particles::Utilities::interpolate_field_on_particles() which uses the
FEPointEvaluation class to interpolate fields on particles efficiently. It is
selected by providing the number of components as a compile-time template
argument, and it takes an arbitrary mapping (defaulting to the reference cell's
default linear mapping), whereas the existing overload deduces the number of
components at run time and evaluates the shape functions directly at the
reference location of each particle.
<br>
(Bruno Blais, 2026/04/14)
